1
00:00:12,195 --> 00:00:13,962
ANNOUNCER:
Welcome to Super Bowl XLVIII

2
00:00:13,964 --> 00:00:19,534
between the Seattle Seahawks
and the Denver Broncos.

3
00:00:19,536 --> 00:00:22,303
The field is a frozen tundra,
(Bart laughing)

4
00:00:22,305 --> 00:00:24,005
imported at great expense
from Alaska.

5
00:00:24,007 --> 00:00:25,473
Hmm?

6
00:00:25,475 --> 00:00:26,508
Hmm?!

7
00:00:26,510 --> 00:00:27,575
Huh...?

8
00:00:28,544 --> 00:00:30,045
(shrieks)

9
00:00:30,047 --> 00:00:31,546
(gasps)

10
00:00:31,548 --> 00:00:32,981
Oh!

11
00:00:32,983 --> 00:00:34,115
(gasps)

12
00:00:35,985 --> 00:00:37,052
(screams)

13
00:00:37,987 --> 00:00:39,254
(screams, jabbers)

14
00:00:44,894 --> 00:00:47,162
(screams, jabbers)

15
00:00:47,164 --> 00:00:48,663
Whoo-hoo.

16
00:00:48,665 --> 00:00:50,198
(whimpers)

17
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,033
(sobs)

18
00:00:52,035 --> 00:00:54,135
(Homer continues
whimpering, sobbing)

19
00:00:55,571 --> 00:00:57,072
(electricity buzzes,
Homer screams and whimpers)

20
00:01:01,243 --> 00:01:02,710
(Homer screams,
electricity crackles)

21
00:01:02,712 --> 00:01:05,013
ANNOUNCER: And the game
comes down to this one play--

22
00:01:05,015 --> 00:01:06,714
(Homer screaming)
a final field goal.

23
00:01:06,716 --> 00:01:08,583
The kick is up,
it hits the crossbar and--

24
00:01:08,585 --> 00:01:09,584
(power humming off)

25
00:01:09,586 --> 00:01:10,885
HOMER:
D'oh!

26
00:01:10,887 --> 00:01:12,287
(Homer slurps beer,
then whoops)

27
00:01:27,403 --> 00:01:31,706
(to tune of "Silver Bells"):
d Glowing rods, glowing rods

28
00:01:31,708 --> 00:01:34,375
d It's making me

29
00:01:34,377 --> 00:01:37,112
d Weak and dizzy...

30
00:01:37,114 --> 00:01:38,780
Uh, rumor has it
they're about to give out

31
00:01:38,782 --> 00:01:40,081
the company Christmas gifts.

32
00:01:40,083 --> 00:01:42,050
Who told you that?

33
00:01:42,052 --> 00:01:43,051
I got an in.

34
00:01:43,053 --> 00:01:43,952
The VP of Personnel

35
00:01:43,954 --> 00:01:46,054
is doing my girlfriend.

36
00:01:46,056 --> 00:01:48,623
Ooh, look at you,
Mr. Connected.

37
00:01:48,625 --> 00:01:51,092
I hope it's better than
last year's lousy gift.

38
00:01:51,094 --> 00:01:52,560
CARL:
Yeah, what a rip.

39
00:01:52,562 --> 00:01:54,095
Ugh. Remember this gift?

40
00:01:54,097 --> 00:01:55,930
The executive stress ball.

41
00:01:55,932 --> 00:01:58,266
BURNS' VOICE: One more squeeze
and you're fired.

42
00:01:58,268 --> 00:02:00,401
(gasps) Now I feel
more stressed than ever.

43
00:02:00,403 --> 00:02:01,903
Gah! (gags)

44
00:02:01,905 --> 00:02:03,738
BURNS' VOICE (muffled):
Excellent.

45
00:02:03,740 --> 00:02:05,907
Excellent. Excellent.

46
00:02:05,909 --> 00:02:08,243
Uh, you don't look
so excellent to me.

47
00:02:08,245 --> 00:02:09,344
(retches)

48
00:02:11,113 --> 00:02:12,914
Ho, ho, humbug.

49
00:02:12,916 --> 00:02:15,416
Santa Claus approaches
to judge and punish.

50
00:02:18,988 --> 00:02:22,090
Wow! A good gift
for once.

51
00:02:22,092 --> 00:02:23,791
Oogle Goggles.

52
00:02:23,793 --> 00:02:25,994
Augmented reality glasses.

53
00:02:25,996 --> 00:02:28,463
You wear them like eyeglasses,
but inside the lens,

54
00:02:28,465 --> 00:02:30,965
you see information about the
people and places around you.

55
00:02:30,967 --> 00:02:34,936
Ooh, finally I'm not a slave
to my stupid human eyeballs.

56
00:02:34,938 --> 00:02:36,838
(gasping in wonder)

57
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,306
HOMER:
Ooh!

58
00:02:38,308 --> 00:02:39,941
Whoa.

59
00:02:39,943 --> 00:02:41,676
(high-pitched gibbering)

60
00:02:43,612 --> 00:02:45,113
(smug chuckling)

61
00:02:45,115 --> 00:02:46,347
Glasses, call Lenny.

62
00:02:46,349 --> 00:02:47,949
Ooh, I'm getting a call.

63
00:02:47,951 --> 00:02:48,950
Answer call.

64
00:02:48,952 --> 00:02:49,984
Hello?

65
00:02:49,986 --> 00:02:52,587
Lenny, it's me, Homer.

66
00:02:54,790 --> 00:02:57,325
Hm. I always thought
it was "Simp-sen."

67
00:02:57,327 --> 00:02:59,961
Really? Don't you ever
look up at the sky?

68
00:02:59,963 --> 00:03:02,197
(theme song playing)

69
00:03:05,134 --> 00:03:06,701
Always wondered
what that was.

70
00:03:07,670 --> 00:03:09,037
Sir, I'm concerned about

71
00:03:09,039 --> 00:03:10,305
your sudden generosity.

72
00:03:10,307 --> 00:03:12,040
The doctor said
to bring you in right away

73
00:03:12,042 --> 00:03:13,541
if you display
kindness or warmth.

74
00:03:13,543 --> 00:03:14,842
Oh, don't worry.

75
00:03:14,844 --> 00:03:17,212
This Santa still has claws.

76
00:03:19,148 --> 00:03:20,982
As of now, each of
those nuclear nitwits

77
00:03:20,984 --> 00:03:22,350
is wearing a
video camera.

78
00:03:22,352 --> 00:03:25,019
With a direct feed to me.

79
00:03:25,021 --> 00:03:26,487
(gasps) You're
spying on them?

80
00:03:26,489 --> 00:03:28,823
Smithers, how much
did this company lose

81
00:03:28,825 --> 00:03:30,892
to office supply
theft last year?

82
00:03:30,894 --> 00:03:32,994
$7,043.

83
00:03:32,996 --> 00:03:35,029
Yes, well, no more of that.

84
00:03:35,031 --> 00:03:37,699
Thanks to this $26 million
surveillance system.

85
00:03:37,701 --> 00:03:38,833
Beware, rabbits.

86
00:03:38,835 --> 00:03:41,569
I spy with my transplanted eyes.

87
00:03:41,571 --> 00:03:44,239
Oh, and I forgot
to show you the best feature.

88
00:03:44,241 --> 00:03:48,076
Each of these buttons
represents an employee.

89
00:03:48,078 --> 00:03:51,279
When I press it,
he or she dies.

90
00:03:55,017 --> 00:03:57,018
(scoffs) What's wrong
with this thing?

91
00:03:57,020 --> 00:03:58,486
(grunts in frustration)

92
00:04:20,042 --> 00:04:21,376
Now, remember kids,

93
00:04:21,378 --> 00:04:23,911
the school says you must
have a valentine card

94
00:04:23,913 --> 00:04:26,080
for everyone in your class.

95
00:04:26,082 --> 00:04:29,584
How does this mean anything
when everyone's forced to do it?

96
00:04:29,586 --> 00:04:31,386
What did I say
about pointing out

97
00:04:31,388 --> 00:04:33,921
the meaninglessness
of things?

98
00:04:33,923 --> 00:04:35,456
Not to.

99
00:04:35,458 --> 00:04:37,058
Well, no way I'm giving
a valentine to Nelson.

100
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:39,260
He's a bully,
and I do not love him.

101
00:04:39,262 --> 00:04:41,396
Jesus says
to love your enemies.

102
00:04:41,398 --> 00:04:43,731
That's because
Jesus knows one day,

103
00:04:43,733 --> 00:04:46,634
he gets to look
his enemies in the eye and say

104
00:04:46,636 --> 00:04:50,104
"It was me who
sent you to Hell."

105
00:04:50,106 --> 00:04:51,773
Bart, your school
requires you

106
00:04:51,775 --> 00:04:53,975
to give everyone
a valentine card

107
00:04:53,977 --> 00:04:56,911
in an envelope
with a fun sticker.

108
00:04:56,913 --> 00:04:59,080
Your teacher
put out an e-mail alert.

109
00:04:59,082 --> 00:05:01,983
With a video attachment.

110
00:05:01,985 --> 00:05:05,253
<i>MAN:
Welcome to Firstline. Tonight,</i>

111
00:05:05,255 --> 00:05:08,256
"Valentine's Day:
Always A Massacre."

112
00:05:08,258 --> 00:05:10,425
<i>At this school,
children may give valentines</i>

113
00:05:10,427 --> 00:05:11,592
<i>to whomever they choose.</i>

114
00:05:11,594 --> 00:05:13,428
<i>Danny is unpopular,</i>

115
00:05:13,430 --> 00:05:17,432
<i>due to rumors he sleeps in the
raw with his ma and his pa.</i>

116
00:05:17,434 --> 00:05:21,102
<i>Human young are born with the
ability to count valentines,</i>

117
00:05:21,104 --> 00:05:23,938
<i>and Danny realizes
he's been snubbed.</i>

118
00:05:23,940 --> 00:05:27,175
Past generations of children
were used to rejection.

119
00:05:27,177 --> 00:05:30,611
But today's kids, raised
in a climate of video games

120
00:05:30,613 --> 00:05:33,448
and instant messaging,
are fragile weirdos.

121
00:05:33,450 --> 00:05:35,783
<i>LYMAN:
On February 15, 2:00am,</i>

122
00:05:35,785 --> 00:05:38,786
<i>after checking
the mailbox one last time,</i>

123
00:05:38,788 --> 00:05:41,189
<i>Danny nearly died
from an overdose</i>

124
00:05:41,191 --> 00:05:42,857
<i>of little candy hearts.</i>

125
00:05:46,128 --> 00:05:49,297
<i>Many of history's monsters
never received a valentine.</i>

126
00:05:49,299 --> 00:05:51,866
<i>Attila the Hun, Mao Tse-tung,</i>

127
00:05:51,868 --> 00:05:53,634
<i>and me, Will Lyman.</i>

128
00:05:53,636 --> 00:05:55,303
<i>This is Firstline.</i>

129
00:05:55,305 --> 00:05:57,805
Fine, Nelson
gets a valentine.

130
00:05:57,807 --> 00:05:59,574
An old one from the box.

131
00:06:02,311 --> 00:06:04,145
Perfect. Bad movie, bad pun,

132
00:06:04,147 --> 00:06:06,247
even bad paper stock.

133
00:06:07,983 --> 00:06:09,183
<i>(Homer laughing)</i>

134
00:06:09,185 --> 00:06:10,685
(giggles)

135
00:06:10,687 --> 00:06:12,387
What's so funny?

136
00:06:12,389 --> 00:06:15,022
I'm watching videos of idiots
wearing these glasses

137
00:06:15,024 --> 00:06:18,159
and not paying attention
to the world around them.

138
00:06:18,161 --> 00:06:19,494
Look at these jerks.

139
00:06:19,496 --> 00:06:21,295
(man screams)

140
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:26,734
Ow!

141
00:06:27,669 --> 00:06:28,736
(man screams)

142
00:06:36,011 --> 00:06:37,678
I don't understand what's
so great about these

143
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:40,848
state of the art,
solar-powered,
computo-glasses.

144
00:06:40,850 --> 00:06:42,016
I'll let you try them on,

145
00:06:42,018 --> 00:06:43,684
right after I decide
if these videos

146
00:06:43,686 --> 00:06:45,052
are Funny Or Die.

147
00:06:45,054 --> 00:06:48,523
Funny, funny, die, die,

148
00:06:48,525 --> 00:06:50,391
funny, funny but
the guy died.

149
00:06:50,393 --> 00:06:52,093
Oh.

150
00:06:52,095 --> 00:06:55,196
Now, a simple Sunday drive
will reveal the hidden wonders

151
00:06:55,198 --> 00:06:57,098
of our hometown.

152
00:07:00,269 --> 00:07:01,402
Hmm...

153
00:07:01,404 --> 00:07:03,471
(grunting with effort)

154
00:07:08,544 --> 00:07:09,477
Whoo-hoo!

155
00:07:11,113 --> 00:07:13,047
D'oh!

156
00:07:13,049 --> 00:07:15,383
Springfield City Hall was built
for the Spencer Tracy movie

157
00:07:15,385 --> 00:07:18,286
<i>Meet Me At City Hall.</i>

158
00:07:18,288 --> 00:07:21,756
It was just a flat wall with
nothing behind it for 30 years.

159
00:07:21,758 --> 00:07:24,459
Dad, Bart's on my side
of the seat.

160
00:07:24,461 --> 00:07:26,961
Dad, Lisa's my
little sister.

161
00:07:26,963 --> 00:07:28,796
(both grunting)

162
00:07:28,798 --> 00:07:31,065
The rearview mirror
was invented in 1911,

163
00:07:31,067 --> 00:07:32,266
for just this reason.

164
00:07:32,268 --> 00:07:33,734
Interesting.

165
00:07:33,736 --> 00:07:35,403
When was the term
"shut up" invented?

166
00:07:35,405 --> 00:07:38,306
As early as 1859,
shut up was used to shut up...

167
00:07:38,308 --> 00:07:40,975
Homie, I think the kids
are just hungry.

168
00:07:40,977 --> 00:07:44,579
Glasses, direct me to the nicest
restaurant I can afford.

169
00:07:44,581 --> 00:07:46,247
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Accessing soup kitchens.

170
00:07:46,249 --> 00:07:49,116
What, you... Oh, that's it,
I'm taking you off.

171
00:07:49,118 --> 00:07:51,252
Aah! Reality.

172
00:07:51,254 --> 00:07:52,186
<i>JEREMY:
Oh! Sorry, sir!</i>

173
00:07:53,322 --> 00:07:56,657
Okay, let's see
what we got here.

174
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:04,932
Ugh, oh! Ooh.

175
00:08:04,934 --> 00:08:06,667
Eh.

176
00:08:10,339 --> 00:08:12,773
Oh.
(Homer giggles)

177
00:08:12,775 --> 00:08:14,275
Mm-hmm.

178
00:08:14,277 --> 00:08:15,943
Squeeze here.

179
00:08:15,945 --> 00:08:17,645
Rotate there.

180
00:08:17,647 --> 00:08:18,946
Pause for sweet talk.

181
00:08:18,948 --> 00:08:21,349
Oh, glasses,
you're so wonderful.

182
00:08:21,351 --> 00:08:24,952
Huh? A-Are you using your
glasses for snuggling?

183
00:08:24,954 --> 00:08:27,822
But the avatar
looks just like you.

184
00:08:27,824 --> 00:08:29,690
I'm afraid wives
don't make passes

185
00:08:29,692 --> 00:08:32,193
at husbands in
those glasses.

186
00:08:33,662 --> 00:08:35,963
Glasses, find me
a great gift for my wife.

187
00:08:35,965 --> 00:08:37,498
(whispers):
Under five dollars.

188
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:39,000
MARGE:
I heard that!

189
00:08:39,002 --> 00:08:41,235
Glasses, take me
two minutes back in time.

190
00:08:48,010 --> 00:08:49,810
Oh... (grumbles)

191
00:08:49,812 --> 00:08:51,979
Marge.
Mm.

192
00:08:51,981 --> 00:08:54,048
About the glasses.
Mm!

193
00:08:54,050 --> 00:08:56,551
I'm really
sorry, and...
Mm, mm, mm.

194
00:08:56,553 --> 00:08:58,653
Here's your breakfast.

195
00:08:58,655 --> 00:09:01,155
Only five pancakes?

196
00:09:01,157 --> 00:09:02,523
You're trying to kill me.

197
00:09:02,525 --> 00:09:04,525
Well, I'm not happy with you.

198
00:09:04,527 --> 00:09:06,494
Look, honey,
I know these glasses

199
00:09:06,496 --> 00:09:08,496
are a radical
new technology

200
00:09:08,498 --> 00:09:10,498
and should be worn
in moderation.

201
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,866
Isn't that right,
glasses?

202
00:09:11,868 --> 00:09:13,868
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Yes, just like I told you.

203
00:09:13,870 --> 00:09:16,370
Anyway, I'm giving them up.

204
00:09:16,372 --> 00:09:19,407
To whoever dares take them.

205
00:09:23,712 --> 00:09:25,913
(Lisa and Bart gasp)

206
00:09:26,882 --> 00:09:27,915
Yoink.

207
00:09:27,917 --> 00:09:29,684
Aw, come on, Mom.

208
00:09:29,686 --> 00:09:32,019
For once,
I'm grabbing the goody.

209
00:09:32,021 --> 00:09:33,921
So the rumors are true.

210
00:09:33,923 --> 00:09:36,424
<i>Moms can want things.</i>

211
00:09:38,594 --> 00:09:40,094
Hmm.

212
00:09:45,367 --> 00:09:46,434
Hmm...

213
00:09:46,436 --> 00:09:48,035
Nicely done, Lewis.

214
00:09:48,037 --> 00:09:52,540
A Transformer
that transforms into a heart?

215
00:09:52,542 --> 00:09:53,774
I love it!

216
00:09:58,046 --> 00:10:00,381
Mm. This Hershey's Kiss
is melted.

217
00:10:00,383 --> 00:10:02,550
Not good.

218
00:10:02,552 --> 00:10:05,052
My mom left it
on the dashboard!

219
00:10:05,054 --> 00:10:06,621
My mom...!

220
00:10:06,623 --> 00:10:08,956
I'll have yours now, Simpson.

221
00:10:11,126 --> 00:10:12,593
In Ga'hoole,

222
00:10:12,595 --> 00:10:14,528
we would break
his frickin' knees.

223
00:10:15,964 --> 00:10:17,098
No.

224
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:19,166
No Valentine
for you, Nelson.

225
00:10:21,069 --> 00:10:22,637
Excuse me?

226
00:10:22,639 --> 00:10:24,305
I'll give a Valentine
to a loser,

227
00:10:24,307 --> 00:10:25,940
I'll give a Valentine to a dork,

228
00:10:25,942 --> 00:10:27,908
I'll even give a Valentine
to a girl,

229
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:31,312
but I won't give a Valentine
to a bully!

230
00:10:31,314 --> 00:10:33,914
Here's what's gonna happen.

231
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:38,085
You have one week to make me the
best Valentine any kid ever got.

232
00:10:38,087 --> 00:10:39,587
And what if I don't?

233
00:10:39,589 --> 00:10:42,256
Simpson, there's gonna be
a heart in my hand,

234
00:10:42,258 --> 00:10:44,859
either paper or yours.

235
00:10:46,962 --> 00:10:48,963
Hey, everybody.
That's strange.

236
00:10:48,965 --> 00:10:52,633
I-I'm hearing a voice,
but I'm not seeing a user icon.

237
00:10:52,635 --> 00:10:55,102
Carl, it's me.
I'm here.

238
00:10:55,104 --> 00:10:56,437
Really here!

239
00:10:56,439 --> 00:10:58,606
Hey, Homer. A lot
of information about you.

240
00:10:58,608 --> 00:11:02,009
Let me just
page through it.
Oh! Stop! Hey! What?

241
00:11:02,011 --> 00:11:05,112
Oh, no one can live
in a non-augmented reality.

242
00:11:05,114 --> 00:11:07,415
I need another pair of glasses.

243
00:11:08,650 --> 00:11:10,951
Charlie, your move
in Muppet Chess.

244
00:11:10,953 --> 00:11:12,953
Gonzo to Fozzie Seven.

245
00:11:12,955 --> 00:11:16,023
Aw! That's Kermit-mate.
Wocka wocka!

246
00:11:16,792 --> 00:11:17,958
Oh, why is it

247
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:19,960
the recipe card
you need is always

248
00:11:19,962 --> 00:11:22,229
the one Homer writes
his cocktail ideas on?

249
00:11:23,865 --> 00:11:26,300
Maybe these
bleep-bloop glasses can help.

250
00:11:26,302 --> 00:11:29,870
Okay, Marge Simpson
entering the Matrix,

251
00:11:29,872 --> 00:11:32,640
for a brownie recipe.

252
00:11:32,642 --> 00:11:35,142
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Here are my top-rated recipes.

253
00:11:35,144 --> 00:11:38,979
Ooh. So many choices, Maggie.

254
00:11:38,981 --> 00:11:41,415
(beeping)

255
00:11:45,053 --> 00:11:47,888
HOMER:
Um, Mr. Burns, sir?

256
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:49,890
Can I get another pair
of glasses?

257
